responded: The older version (ref 5604191) has the method addRootCert with a slightly different signature and implementation compared to the newer version patch. The older version method uses FilesystemKeystoreInformation and calls findRootCert with location and password parameters, while the newer version uses a more generic KeystoreInformation and calls findRootCert with the keystoreInformation object and alias.

The method addCertificates exists in both versions but in the older version it uses cert.getSubjectX500Principal().getName() as the alias for setCertificateEntry, while the newer version uses generateAlias(this.truststore, cert).

The new method addFromKeystore and the helper method toX509Certs do not exist in the older version.

The patch to be backported changes addRootCert to remove it and replace it with addFromKeystore which adds the entire certificate chain instead of just the root cert. It also changes addCertificates to use generateAlias instead of cert.getSubjectX500Principal().getName().

Given this, the patch is not a simple context change but introduces new methods and changes existing method signatures and logic.

